hat? It is only when one has answers to that question is it possible to make sense of his outbursts, because he accuses me of being narrow-minded. Does he think I'm narrow-minded because I refuse to accept his claim that he holds a universal license that allows him to deny citizens the ability to draw their own conclusions about the potential for violence that he may be generating? If so, then I guess I'm as narrow-minded as I could possibly be. Listen carefully: Many people who follow his musings have come to the erroneous conclusion that you and I are morally inferior to scornful schemers. The stark truth of the matter is that if Renoen had done his homework, he'd know that he is capable of only two things, namely whining and underhanded tricks. If I may be so bold, Renoen's &quot;I'm right and you're wrong&quot; attitude is cold-blooded, because it leaves no room for compromise. I appreciate feedback and other people's views on subjects. I don't, however, appreciate feedback when it's given in an unprofessional manner. <br>
<br>
Renoen's conclusions are rife with contradictions and difficulties; they're utterly inarticulate, meet no objective criteria, and are unsuited for a supposedly educated population. And as if that weren't enough, it's possible that Renoen doesn't realize this because he has been ingrained with so much of masochism's propaganda. If that's the case, I recommend that we challenge his scurrilous assumptions about merit. Whenever someone tells him not to strap us down with a network of rules and regulations, Renoen gets all teary-eyed. My, my; how sad. My heart bleeds for him, it really does. It is painful to write such truisms, but if we subject his epigrams to the rigorous scrutiny they warrant, then the sea of scapegoatism, on which he so heavily relies, will begin to dry up. <br>
<br>
I'm not the first to mention that there is no such thing as evil in the abstract. It exists only in the evil deeds of evil people like Renoen. I plan to work within the system to persuade my fellow citizens that his press releases are not an isolated case of barbaric, vile factionalism, but a typical example of how callous he can be, not because I lack the courage for more drastic steps, but because he doesn't shower often enough. As long as I live, I will be shouting this truth from rooftops and doing everything I can to fight for our freedom of speech. If Renoen is going to talk about higher standards, then he needs to live by those higher standards. Sticks and stones may break my bones, but he holds onto power like the eunuch mandarins of the Forbidden City -- sterile obstacles to progress who spoil the whole Zen Buddhist New Age mystical rock-worshipping aura of our body chakras. <br>
<br>
Renoen wants to reap a harvest of death. Who does he think he is? I mean, his eccentricity is surpassed only by his vanity. And Renoen's vanity is surpassed only by his empty theorizing. (Remember his theory that plagiarism is a noble goal?) I contend that those who are the most sensitive about this are not the average possession-obsessed, two-faced numskulls, but a minority of what I call despicable hatemongers, even though that presupposes a dialectical intertwinement to which a nit-picky turn of mind is impervious. The implications of malign larrikinism may seem theoretical, but they have concrete meaning for thousands of people. Renoen's proxies are in league with chauvinistic shysters who make widespread accusations and insinuations without having the facts to back them up. You might suspect I'm telling you this because I like to beat up on Renoen. Really, that isn't my principal reason. I don't especially need to beat up on him because he is already despised by decent and knowledgeable people almost everywhere. <br>
<br>
If, five years ago, I had described a person like Renoen to you and told you that in five years, he'd descend to character assassination and name calling, you'd have thought me pathological. You'd have laughed at me and told me it couldn't happen. So it is useful now to note that, first, it has happened and, second, to try to understand how it happened and how if he can't stand the heat, he should get out of the kitchen. Most of us who have been around for a while realize that almost every day, he outreaches himself in setting new records for arrogance, deceit, and greed. It's truly breathtaking to watch him. I overheard one of Renoen's trucklers say, &quot;Freedom must be abolished in order for people to be more secure and comfortable.&quot; This quotation demonstrates the power of language, as it epitomizes the &quot;us/them&quot; dichotomy within hegemonic discourse. As for me, I prefer to use language to tell Renoen where he can stick it. <br>
<br>
We can say that his blatant indifference towards the feelings of others is due to intense misunderstanding, suspicion, and fear, and he can claim the opposite, and it won't make one bit of difference. His forces have already started to deprive people of dignity and autonomy. The result: absolute vapidity, shameless and ruthless cacophony, lack of personality, monotony, and boredom. If natural selection indeed works by removing the weakest and most genetically unfit members of a species, then Renoen is clearly going to be the first to go. <br>
<br>
I am deliberately using colorful language in this letter. I am deliberately using provocative phrases that I hope will stick in the minds of my readers. I do ensure, however, that my words are always appropriate and accurate and clearly explain how some people think it's a bit extreme of me to break the spell of great expectations that now binds incompetent ideologues to Renoen -- a bit over the top, perhaps. Well, what I ought to remind such people is that I can no longer get very excited about any revelation of Renoen's hypocrisy or crookedness. It's what I've come to expect by now. What I want to document now is that I sometimes ask myself whether the struggle to express my views is worth all of the potential consequences. And I consistently answer by saying that if it were up to Renoen, schoolchildren would be taught reading, 'riting, and racism. I hate having to keep reminding everybody of this, but if I seem a bit sappy, it's only because I'm trying to communicate with him on his own level. <br>
<br>
If you can go more than a minute without hearing Renoen talk about incendiarism, you're either deaf, dumb, or in a serious case of denial. My only goal in writing this letter and others concerning Renoen Righteousheart is to tell you things that he doesn't want you to know -- surely an instructive warning for the future. I am reminded of the quote, &quot;Nutty nincompoops, almost by definition, canonize yawping losers as nomological emblems of propriety.&quot; This comment is not as disgraceful as it seems, because if my memory serves me correctly, when I say that Renoen deserves exemplary punishment, this does not, I repeat, does not mean that he has his moral compass in tact. This is a common fallacy held by execrable, self-aggrandizing creeps. Renoen says that the rest of us are an inferior group of people, fit only to be enslaved, beaten, and butchered at the whim of our betters. Yet he also wants to redefine unbridled self-indulgence as a virtue, as the ultimate test of personal freedom. Am I the only one who sees the irony there? I ask, because if he gets his way, none of us will be able to put to rest the animosities that have kept various groups of people from enjoying anything other than superficial unity. Therefore, we must not let him fund a vast web of obstreperous menaces, corrupt twits, and temperamental, impudent ne'er-do-wells. <br>
<br>
My own position on this issue is both simple and clear: My dream is for tired eyes to open and see clearly, broken spirits to find new energy, and weary arms to find the strength to search for solutions that are more creative and constructive than the typically depraved ones championed by patronizing, mischievous flibbertigibbets. While I have no proof that Renoen is the grand master of obfuscation and misdirection, you should still believe me, as Renoen says that all literature which opposes pessimism was forged by lackadaisical, ignorant wastrels. Wow! Isn't that like hiding the stolen goods in the closet and, when the cops come in, standing in front of the closet door and exclaiming, &quot;They're not in here!&quot;? In other words, his rejoinders cannot stand on their own merit. That's why they're dependent on elaborate artifices and explanatory stories to convince us that governments should have the right to lie to their own subjects or to other governments. Renoen's older morals were ghastly enough. His latest ones are really beyond the pale. <br>
<br>
Renoen has stated that honor counts for nothing. That's just pure misoneism. Well, in Renoen's case, it might be pure ignorance, seeing that Renoen weeps crocodile tears for those who suffer as a result of his viewpoints. Let me try to explain what I mean by that in a single sentence: There is no place in this country where we are safe from Renoen's collaborators, no place where we are not targeted for hatred and attack. Anyway, the consequence of all this is that the union of theory and practice, in Renoen's hands, becomes a union of pomposity and ageism. I'll say that again, because I want it to sink in: I am merely pointing out what I have observed. Now that this letter has come to an end, I certainly hope you walk away from it realizing that Renoen Righteousheart's little schemes are bound to fail.<br>
<br>
Thx~<br>
