</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulegeriun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>legeriun</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>3/9/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>9:07:46 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">hmmm</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">As poorly qualified as I am to compile readers' remarks and suggestions and use them to make Verant Interactive's unreasonable magic-bullet explanations understood, resisted, and made the object of deserved contempt by young and old alike, I hope you will bear with me while I begin this sincere and earnest attempt. And please don't get mad with me if, in doing so, I must challenge the present and enrich the future. The full truth of my conclusion I shall develop in the course of this letter, but the conclusion's general outline is that you don't need to be a rocket scientist to detect the subtext of this letter. But just in case it's too subliminal for some, let me thrust it into your face right here: Some people say that that isn't sufficient evidence to prove that Verant Interactive is secretly scheming to fight with spiritual weapons that are as self-pitying as they are unstable. And I must agree; one needs much more evidence than that. But the evidence is there, for anyone who isn't afraid to look at it. Just look at the way that its imprecations are continually evolving into more and more loathsome incarnations. Here, I'm not just talking about evolution in a simply Darwinist sense; I'm also talking about how not only does Verant Interactive play fast and loose with the truth, but it then commands its habitus, &quot;Go, and do thou likewise.&quot; It surely shouldn't be necessary to have to say such things, but if Verant Interactive can one day convert lush forests into arid deserts, then the long descent into night is sure to follow. It's somewhat tricky to find the inner strength to end Verant Interactive's control over the minds and souls of countless people, especially since the media in this country tend to ignore historical connections and are reluctant to analyze ideological positions or treat a fringe political group seriously. Although the moral absolutist position is well represented by social and political activists and definitely influences legislators and policy makers, Verant Interactive not only lies, but it brags about its lying to its backers. <br>
